Explore our beginnings



                                            Our unparalleled technology and expert traders excel under the best and the worst market conditions.					








SINCE THE START
We've never stopped growing and innovating
Trillium’s core management team pioneered the electronic trading industry, beginning their careers in the mid-1990s.








Our Progress




ISLAND ECN
The first electronic order matching system, now the foundation of NASDAQ's system architecture




DATEK ONLINE
A retail online trading business sold to Ameritrade for $1.3 billion in 2002, and now known as TD Ameritrade




TRILLIUM TRADING
Trillium, a premier trading and technology firm, is established in 2003




TRILLIUM LABS
In 2013, Trillium's in-house software development group spun off and became Trillium Labs 




SURVEYOR
In 2014, Trillium launched its first public product, the enterprise trade surveillance software Surveyor




CHICAGO
Trillium's presence expands westward with the opening of a new Chicago trading floor in 2015











In April 2016 Trillium was honored to host the Nasdaq Closing Bell Ceremony.
Trillium Surveyor was honored on April 29th, 2016 to be invited by Nasdaq to host the Closing Bell Ceremony and ring the market out for the day.
